  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Most people experience stress at some point in their lives. Stress, especially when severe,
      can not only make you feel bad, it can also worsen existing health problems like heart
      disease, type 2 diabetes, obesity, high blood pressure, depression, and even cancer. Healthy
      Mind, Healthy You is a new study about how mindfulness can help people cope with stress.
      Funded by the Patient Centered Outcome Research Institute (PCORI) and involving 19 Patient
      Powered Research Networks (PPRNs), Healthy Mind Healthy You will be able to study the effects
      of mindfulness on a wide variety of populations and conditions.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
